<br>
Being a wood elf I mostly like the trade skill update, especially as I've always worked quite a bit to keep my tailoring up. My only concern is that tailoring has no semi cheap things we can use to get above 115 skill. I mean, making racial leathers is obviously very very time consuming and quite expensive. I would have liked to seen them add something using lion hides (one of the few unused skin types) with a trivial of 140-150. Possibly fleeting quivers. The one thing I have no idea what to do about though are the skins, I doubt I could solo a tiger on my own and convincing friends to go kill greens who drop nothing but pelts will be.. challenging. *sigh* and of course as *always* I get the joy of trying to find morning dew. Honestly, that @#%$ is used in brewing, smithing and now I need it to tailor racial leather - I'm surprised they haven't found a way to work it into baking, fletching and jewelry yet. And it's only foragable by rangers and druids. I'm really sick of seeing every other recipe have morning dew as a component, some originality would be nice. If it at least dropped randomly of say pixies or fairies I wouldn't mind.<br>
<br>
